Homa Bay County Referral Hospital has been faced with acute shortage of water and power outage for a week. The hospital has not paid bills amounting to Sh1 million for both electricity and water.County KMPDU chairman Ben Otieno said operations have been hurt.&ldquo;We&rsquo;ve been reduced to using candles to perform operations at night. The only generator we have has broken down,&rdquo; he said.Otieno said health workers work under difficult conditions, and the situation has been worsened by the shortage of medical supply.For two days, patients&rsquo; caretakers have asked that they be discharged.Damaris Atieno, 42, requested the hospital&rsquo;s administration to discharge her ailing husband following the crisis.&ldquo;I&rsquo;ve spent the little money I had in buying candles for night use. We can&rsquo;t get food because they lack water at the hospital,&rdquo; she said. Health executive Lawrence Oteng&rsquo; acknowledged the challenge and said they are working to resolve the situation.